      "text": "- Meta has a tough time selling its metaverse ideas. It now publishes figures for Reality Labs which is their department very much in charge of all things metaverse. In the fourth quarter they suffered an operational loss of 3.3 billion dollar for 877 million dollar revenue. This comes at a time when they get heavy pressure on the growth of the ad-revenue because of privacy measures by Apple and behavioral shifts of the users. Investors are not amused, the stock went down 20% after the announcements. "
